\f0\b\fs66 \cf0 Shoyu Chicken\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\fs40 \cf2 Yield:  \cf0 6 to 8 servings\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa240\ql\qnatural

\fs52 \cf0 INGREDIENTS\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl260\sa280\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\b0\fs48 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}5 1/2 to 6 pounds chicken thighs\
{\listtext	\'95	}5 cups low-sodium chicken broth\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 cups low-sodium soy sauce\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 cup packed light brown sugar\
{\listtext	\'95	}3/4 cup mirin\
{\listtext	\'95	}8 medium garlic cloves, smashed and peeled\
{\listtext	\'95	}4-inch piece ginger, sliced 1/2-inch thick and smashed\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl260\sa280\ql\qnatural
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}1 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper\
{\listtext	\'95	}5 tablespoons cornstarch dissolved in 5 tablespoons water\
{\listtext	\'95	}Thinly sliced green onions, for garnish\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa240\ql\qnatural

\b\fs52 \cf0 DIRECTIONS\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl380\sa160\ql\qnatural

\b0\fs48 \cf3 Combine all ingredients except cornstarch and green onions in a large pot and bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce to low and simmer, covered, turning occasionally, until chicken is tender, about 30 to 35 minutes more. \uc0\u8232 \u8232 Remove chicken to a serving platter. Remove garlic and ginger and discard. Bring sauce to a boil, skim off excess fat, and cook until reduced slightly, about 10 minutes. Whisk in cornstarch mixture and bring to a boil. Remove from heat, add chicken, turn to coat, and serve chicken with sauce and sliced green onions. \
